{
  "stem": "2533.2",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And then they were executed.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But we-- I didn't know.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We didn't know straight away what happened to them.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Only later I found out.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, no.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In Siedliszcze, yes.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That morning, it was a very, very bleak morning in Staw, and we were-- it was-- the whole world was covered in snow.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But somehow the-- the sky looked a bit red.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We couldn't understand it.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I still can see the red sky in the middle of the winter.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we were all on the wagons, like my mother, my sister, and the youngest brother.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And my other brother was with my father.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we were driving along.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And then when we came to a crossroad, it was-- to the right was to Chelm and to the left to Siedliszcze or vice versa.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And when the wagons were turning to Vlodava-- not Siedliszcze, Wlodawa.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Sorry.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "To Wlodawa.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "My youngest brother, who was on the same wagon with me and my sister, he said-- we heard certain things on what was going on in Sobibor.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But that was-- we thought it was only rumors.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "But I don't know from where he knew maybe more than we did.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "He said to my mother, let's say goodbye to the night, because we won't see this-- the daylight.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My youngest.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He was only 11 then.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And when we come to Sobibor, it was about 8 o'clock at night.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the whole camp was lit.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It was like daylight.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The-- music was playing.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we were told to get off the-- the wagons.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The wagons drove away.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The men separate, so my youngest brother went to-- with my father, and I stayed with my sister and mother.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then a big, tall German came along and stand on a-- on-- on-- like a platform.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
